HEADWORD: Struvite
<hw>Struv"ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[After the Russian
minister Von <ets>Struve</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A
crystalline mineral found in guano. It is a hydrous phosphate of
magnesia and ammonia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

